NAME: bes-test-async.sh	(submits jobs asynchronously)

DESCRIPTION:	This script runs uses the jsdl files in this directory to test asynchronous BES job submission, stage-in and  stage-out 

INPUT:	inputfile.txt
	Contents of inputfile.txt
	GENII_INSTALL_DIR : GenesisII client is installation path
	DEPLOYMENT_NAME	: deployment name you want to use (usually default)
	GENII_USER_DIR : GenesisII state directory path (usually ~/.genesisII-2.0)
	QUEUE_PATH  : Path tp Grid queue on which jobs will be submitted
	RNSPATH  : Grid path where you can stage-in and stage out the files. 

OUTPUT:		status.out

USAGE/EXAMPLE:	
	
LIMITATIONS:	Should have properly set all the environment variables in inputfile.txt

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME: bes-test-submission-point.sh	(submits jobs to BES submission point)

DESCRIPTION:	This script tests a very specific feature of GenesisII BES, which is that they support a directory where jobs can be submitted by simply copying them in, and where the running jobs can be queried in a state area.

INPUT:	inputfile.txt
	Contents of inputfile.txt
	GENII_INSTALL_DIR : GenesisII client is installation path
	DEPLOYMENT_NAME	: deployment name you want to use (usually default)
	GENII_USER_DIR : GenesisII state directory path (usually ~/.genesisII-2.0)
	QUEUE_PATH  : Path tp Grid queue on which jobs will be submitted
	RNSPATH  : Grid path where you can stage-in and stage out the files. 

OUTPUT:		status.out

USAGE/EXAMPLE:	
	
LIMITATIONS:	Should have properly set all the environment variables in inputfile.txt

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:	ls-single-job.jsdl
	
DESCRIPTION:	Submits a single 'ls' job to specified queue

INPUT:	N/A

OUTPUT: Ticket Number for the job

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path> local:<local-path>/ls-single-job.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:	hostname-sleep-60s.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:	Submits a single 'hostname' job to specified queue, job sleeps for 60s

INPUT:	N/A

OUTPUT:	Ticket Number for the job 

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path> local:<local-path>/hostname-sleep-60s.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: 	None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:	hostname-stage-out.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:	Submits a single 'hostname' job to specified queue, stages-out the output.txt to user's grid home directory

INPUT: 	N/A

OUTPUT: Ticket Number for the job, output.txt 

USAGE/EXAMPLE: <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path> local:<local-path>/hostname-stage-out.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: None

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NAME:	cat-stdin-stageout.jsdl

DESCRIPTION:	Submits a 'cat' job that takes filename as input and cat's the filename to a output file.

INPUT:	File name to be 'cat'

OUTPUT: File that has 'cat' output (cat.out, cat.err)

USAGE/EXAMPLE:  <GenesisII-Install-Dir>/grid qsub <grid-queue-path> local:<local-path>/cat-stdin-stageout.jsdl

LIMITATIONS: Input file name should exist

